3599
03:00:14,420 --> 03:00:20,640
Valence electrons are the electrons in the outermost shell of an atom, the ones that determine

3600
03:00:20,640 --> 03:00:24,240
how an element bonds, reacts, and behaves chemically.

3601
03:00:24,440 --> 03:00:25,800
Bismuth has five.

3602
03:00:26,180 --> 03:00:29,400
Muscovium, or element 115, has five.

3603
03:00:29,640 --> 03:00:35,220
They sit in the same column of the periodic table, group 15, which means they have essentially

3604
03:00:35,220 --> 03:00:41,180
the same chemical personality, the same bonding geometry, the same family of crystal structures,

3605
03:00:41,180 --> 03:00:47,420
the same tendency to form the layered compounds that produce the most exotic quantum behavior

3606
03:00:47,420 --> 03:00:49,340
known to material science.

3607
03:00:49,560 --> 03:00:54,600
