3615
03:01:24,600 --> 03:01:28,300
Bismuth is one of the most unusual elements on the periodic table.

3616
03:01:28,300 --> 03:01:30,820
Most high-K materials are passive.

3617
03:01:31,160 --> 03:01:33,960
They sit there, holding charge, and do nothing else.

3618
03:01:34,260 --> 03:01:35,340
Bismuth is different.

3619
03:01:35,880 --> 03:01:37,000
It fights back.

3620
03:01:37,860 --> 03:01:43,340
Expose bismuth to a magnetic field, and instead of being attracted the way iron pushes towards

3621
03:01:43,340 --> 03:01:45,320
a magnet, it pushes away.

3622
03:01:46,120 --> 03:01:52,020
This property is called diamagnetism, and bismuth has more of it than any other stable element

3623
03:01:52,020 --> 03:01:58,260
on Earth, not slightly more, dramatically, anomalously, inexplicably more.

3624
03:01:59,880 --> 03:02:03,100
